What an evening!

Career Compass 2025 was an incredible night, and we want to extend our gratitude to everyone who made it possible! 

A huge thank you to all the amazing firms, panelists, and networking reps for sharing your time, stories, and advice. To the student clubs behind the scenes — GCG, MINT, CAINZ, BusinessOne, and DSCubed — and all the dedicated directors and officers who brought this event to life, we’re so grateful for your hard work. And to all the attendees who came with curiosity and asked thoughtful questions — thank you for making the evening what it was! ✨

From insightful panel discussions to meaningful chats during networking, it was a night full of opportunities and career growth! We hope you walked away feeling motivated and ready to take on the road ahead! 🚀

Swipe through to revisit the highlights! ➡️

🎉 Thank you everyone for making Kaggle Competition 2025 a huge success! 🎉

On Saturday, May 3rd, we hosted our biggest Kaggle Competition to date – and what an incredible turnout it was!
 
Our club’s unique datathon event challenged participants to tackle real-world machine learning and prediction tasks in a fast-paced, 3-hour coding sprint. Using sports datasets, participants built models to predict the ladder positions of AFL teams, putting their impressive data science and ML skills to the test in a collaborative and competitive environment.

🏆Winners!🏆
1st Place ($200 + Jane Street Merch + DS3 merch) – Dimitri Micha von Benckendorff, Lakshminarasimhan Sudarshan
2nd Place ($150 + Jane Street Merch + DS3 merch) – Lee Han Hsiang, Muhammad Azad bin Mohamed Afif
3rd Place ($100 + Jane Street Merch + DS3 merch) – Ebyn Chan

A huge congratulations to our winners and to all participants who took on the challenge with enthusiasm and creativity. Your energy and talent made this competition truly special.

🙏 A massive shoutout to our Education Team!
We couldn’t have done it without you. From building the custom dataset and setting up the Kaggle platform to delivering insightful workshops and walkthroughs, your efforts were exceptional and continue to shape and grow the educational heart of our club.

👏 And of course, a big thank you to our IT Team for building the stunning Kaggle Competition website, and our Events Team and on-the-day volunteers for making sure everything ran smoothly behind the scenes.

Most importantly, we hope everyone had fun and walked away with new skills, insights and connections! You are all amazing!

🚀 We’ll be back with even bigger things – stay tuned for more!
